# Dev environment

This project lives on the `/Volumes/JohnDovey` external drive. Environment variables are set by `/Volumes/JohnDovey/source-john-dovey.sh`, auto-sourced from the shell rc whenever the drive is mounted:

- `ANDROID_HOME=/Volumes/JohnDovey/Android/Sdk`
- `GRADLE_USER_HOME=/Volumes/JohnDovey/.gradle`
- `JAVA_HOME=/usr/local/opt/openjdk@17/libexec/openjdk.jdk/Contents/Home` (Homebrew openjdk@17)
- PATH additions: Android `tools`/`platform-tools`, `$JAVA_HOME/bin`, plus the OpenCode and OpenClaw CLI tools (also homed on the volume).

Any build or run script added to this project should `source ~/source-john-dovey.sh --quiet` at the top before invoking Gradle/Android tooling, rather than hardcoding SDK/Java paths. See also `android-build.mdc` and `volume-storage.mdc`.
